Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.digidoc4j.impl.asic.xades.XadesSignature.getOCSPResponseCreationTime()
    use Signature.getOCSPResponseCreationTime() instead. Will be removed in the future.
    org.digidoc4j.SignatureParameters.getProductionPlace() 
    org.digidoc4j.impl.ddoc.DDocFacade.getSignature(int)
    will be removed in the future.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.getTslDataLoaderFactory()
    Prefer to use Configuration.setTslFileLoaderFactory(DSSFileLoaderFactory) and Configuration.getTslFileLoaderFactory() instead. If a custom TSL file loader factory is configured, then a custom TSL data loader factory has no effect. If a data loader created by a custom TSL data loader factory does not implement DSSFileLoader, then it is wrapped into a FileCacheDataLoader.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.getTslKeyStoreLocation()
    Use Configuration.getLotlTruststorePath() instead.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.getTslKeyStorePassword()
    Use Configuration.getLotlTruststorePassword() instead.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.getTslLocation()
    Use Configuration.getLotlLocation() instead.
    org.digidoc4j.impl.asic.SKCommonCertificateVerifier.setDataLoader(DataLoader)
    org.digidoc4j.SignatureParameters.setProductionPlace(SignatureProductionPlace) 
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.setTslDataLoaderFactory(DataLoaderFactory)
    Prefer to use Configuration.setTslFileLoaderFactory(DSSFileLoaderFactory) and Configuration.getTslFileLoaderFactory() instead. If a custom TSL file loader factory is configured, then a custom TSL data loader factory has no effect. If a data loader created by a custom TSL data loader factory does not implement DSSFileLoader, then it is wrapped into a FileCacheDataLoader.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.setTslKeyStoreLocation(String)
    Use Configuration.setLotlTruststorePath(String) instead.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.setTslKeyStorePassword(String)
    Use Configuration.setLotlTruststorePassword(String) instead.
    org.digidoc4j.Configuration.setTslLocation(String)
    Use Configuration.setLotlLocation(String) instead.
